# Keep root docs in sync

After implementing a feature or otherwise notable change (new component, store
field, utility script, npm script, config behavior, etc.), update both
[README.md](../../README.md) and [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) in the same
change so they stay accurate — don't leave this for a separate/later pass.

- `README.md` is user-facing: update the feature list, "Utility scripts"
  section, screenshots, or setup/commands sections as relevant to what
  changed.
- `CLAUDE.md` is agent-facing: update the "Architecture" bullets, add/update a
  `## utils/<toolName>` section for new utility scripts, or add a "Notes" bullet
  for any non-obvious gotcha introduced by the change.

Skip this for pure refactors, bug fixes, or internal changes with no
user-visible or architecturally-relevant effect — don't pad the docs with
noise. When in doubt, prefer a small accurate update over none.
